                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13998615" author="mreutegg" created="Thu, 15 May 2014 09:22:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added test with some refactoring in &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1594835&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1594835&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14001653" author="mreutegg" created="Mon, 19 May 2014 12:50:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1595875&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1595875&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14003198" author="mreutegg" created="Tue, 20 May 2014 13:12:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The fix requires a MongoDB 2.6 feature (the $max operator) and breaks the build on travis, which still uses 2.4.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14003205" author="mreutegg" created="Tue, 20 May 2014 13:18:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Reverted the changes in &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1596233&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1596233&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14006043" author="mmarth" created="Thu, 22 May 2014 15:45:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mreutegg&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mreutegg&quot;&gt;mreutegg&lt;/a&gt;, I think we should backport this fix (once done) to 1.0. Diff calculations are so central to Oak that I suspect incorrect ones to cause all sorts of problems. WDYT?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14027492" author="mreutegg" created="Wed, 11 Jun 2014 06:57:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, definitively makes sense. Added 1.0.1 fix version.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14027572" author="mreutegg" created="Wed, 11 Jun 2014 09:26:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As of &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1601838&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1601838&lt;/a&gt; travis will now use MongoDB 2.6.1. With this commit I also re-applied the fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14027673" author="mreutegg" created="Wed, 11 Jun 2014 12:01:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Merged revisions 1594835,1594888,1601838 from trunk to 1.0 branch: &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1601865&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1601865&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
